Uses of Package
common

  • Packages that use common 
    Package Description
    common
    Core framework classes, and application-independent classes and data, such as:
        SFDC object types
        constants and utility methods
        page and window metadata
    gdw
    Global Data Warehouse (GDW) classes and data, such as:
        SFDC object types
        constants and utility methods
        page and window metadata
        test code and test properties
    lm
    Leads Management (LM) classes and data, such as:
        SFDC object types
        constants and utility methods
        page and window metadata
        test code and test properties
    mja
    Major Accounts (MJA) classes and data, such as:
        SFDC object types
        constants and utility methods
        page and window metadata
        test code and test properties
    ss
    Sales & Support (SS) classes and data, such as:
        SFDC object types
        constants and utility methods
        page and window metadata
        test code and test properties
  • Classes in common used by common 
    Class and Description
    Address
    Representation of an address, as implemented in SFDC objects.
    ApprovalChain.Chain 
    ApprovalRoleCode
    Discount Approval Request (DAR) approval role codes.
    Approver.ApproverDetails 
    Contact
    Representation of an application-independent SFDC Contact.
    DiscountApprovalRequest
    Representation of an MJA Discount Approval Request.
    DiscountCategory.DiscountCategoryDetails 
    DiscountCategory.RoutingCriteriaLine 
    DiscountCategory.RoutingCriteriaTable 
    DiscountCategoryCode
    Discount Approval Request (DAR) discount category codes.
    EISConstants.AlertResponseType
    Tokens for use in dismissing alerts.
    EISConstants.App
    References to EIS applications, typically used for performing application-specific actions in application-independent levels of the framework.
    EISConstants.DateOffsetType
    Tokens specified in the value property when declaring FieldData objects. They allow specifying a positive or negative offset to a current date.
    EISConstants.FieldExistenceCheckType
    Values returned by methods that verify the existence or non-existence of a field
    EISConstants.FieldType
    Field types for use in declaring Field objects.
    EISConstants.FieldVisibilityCheckType
    Values returned by methods that verify the visibility or non-visibility of a field
    EISConstants.PageVerificationCategoryType
    Verification categories for use by page-scope verification methods that verify FieldData objects using closely related verification types.
    EISConstants.ParameterizedLocatorType
    Special locator types for use in declaring some Field objects (tables, related lists, and info panels).
    EISConstants.ParameterizedTestDataValueType
    Test data types for use in declaring FieldData objects. They expect a delimited parameter representing the test data value.
    EISConstants.ParameterizedVerificationDataValueType
    Verification types for use in declaring FieldData objects.
    EISConstants.RequirednessLevel
    'Requiredness' level types for use in declaring Field objects.
    EISConstants.TestResultType
    Test result types for use in test properties file metadata.
    Field
    Representation of a field (input or read-only) on a page in an SFDC application.
    FieldData_
    Defines required methods for classes that define test data and verification data objects.
    FieldDataInstance_
    Defines required methods for classes that define instances of FieldData_ objects.
    FieldDependencySet
    Representation of a set of prerequisite and dependent Field objects, used for enforcing the order in which Field objects are accessible on a page.
    Oppty
    Representation of an application-independent SFDC Opportunity.
    Org
    Representation of an SFDC organization.
    Page_
    Defines required public methods for classes that define Page objects.
    Product
    Representation of an application-independent SFDC Product.
    Rdbms 
    SFDCObject
    Describes features and functionality common to all SFDC objects.
    TestProperties
    Manages all test data, verification data, and metadata in test properties files.
    Window_
    Defines required public methods for classes that define Window objects.
